from those soul wounds?

00:40:12.450 --> 00:40:15.930 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: You know, I
provide practical tools--

00:40:15.930 --> 00:40:17.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:40:17.310 --> 00:40:21.000 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: --in my sessions,
where you have to identify.

00:40:21.000 --> 00:40:23.380 align:middle line:84%
Because you can't heal
from what you don't know.

00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:24.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:40:24.180 --> 00:40:25.920 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: Can you
sit down and think

00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:32.340 align:middle line:84%
about the soul wounds, those
generational wounds that

00:40:32.340 --> 00:40:33.960 align:middle line:90%
had been passed to you?

00:40:33.960 --> 00:40:35.585 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:40:35.585 --> 00:40:36.960 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: The
things, the wounds

00:40:36.960 --> 00:40:41.610 align:middle line:84%
that bring fear,
hesitation in our life.

00:40:41.610 --> 00:40:44.010 align:middle line:84%
When you track
those things, you'll

00:40:44.010 --> 00:40:47.340 align:middle line:84%
find there is a
grandmother, there

00:40:47.340 --> 00:40:50.850 align:middle line:84%
is a grandfather who
also went through that.

00:40:50.850 --> 00:40:52.420 align:middle line:90%
I believe in epigenetics.

00:40:52.420 --> 00:40:53.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:40:53.220 --> 00:40:56.550 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: The trauma that
was passed from one generation

00:40:56.550 --> 00:40:59.380 align:middle line:84%
to the next, it becomes
part of our DNA.

00:40:59.380 --> 00:41:00.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:41:00.180 --> 00:41:03.240 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: But we need
to reflect back and look

00:41:03.240 --> 00:41:06.840 align:middle line:84%
at that trauma, where
it's coming from,

00:41:06.840 --> 00:41:13.090 align:middle line:84%
what it is shaping in our lives,
confront it, write it down.

00:41:13.090 --> 00:41:17.160 align:middle line:84%
That's why I tell you
about I write every day.

00:41:17.160 --> 00:41:20.550 align:middle line:90%
I confront my fears every day.

00:41:20.550 --> 00:41:24.180 align:middle line:84%
I confront my soul
wounds every day.

00:41:24.180 --> 00:41:28.390 align:middle line:84%
And I ask myself and I am
asking to the women, what

00:41:28.390 --> 00:41:31.440 align:middle line:90%
soul wounds do you carry?

00:41:31.440 --> 00:41:34.500 align:middle line:90%
Is this what's shaping you?

00:41:34.500 --> 00:41:36.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And shaping the
lives of your children.

00:41:36.790 --> 00:41:37.950 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:41:37.950 --> 00:41:43.080 align:middle line:84%
Because when we are silent about
that, we pass on that silencing

00:41:43.080 --> 00:41:45.360 align:middle line:84%
to the next generation,
to our children.

00:41:45.360 --> 00:41:46.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:41:46.480 --> 00:41:50.250 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: So I provide
those tools for women

00:41:50.250 --> 00:41:55.380 align:middle line:84%
to really dig deep and
tap into those traumas

00:41:55.380 --> 00:41:58.710 align:middle line:84%
and then we begin
to find healing.

00:41:58.710 --> 00:42:02.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've recently gone
