>>LISA: Because she's
been caring for my father

00:44:14.298 --> 00:44:16.660 align:middle line:84%
for so long and he's
been sick for so long.

00:44:16.660 --> 00:44:18.820 align:middle line:84%
And she always
had cared for him.

00:44:18.820 --> 00:44:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And so finally she
gets her voice heard.

00:44:23.310 --> 00:44:25.260 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: The
awakening of her voice.

00:44:25.260 --> 00:44:26.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:44:26.060 --> 00:44:29.110 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: Reclaiming our
voices, it's very important.

00:44:29.110 --> 00:44:33.430 align:middle line:84%
Because I always tell women
you don't claim the voice.

00:44:33.430 --> 00:44:34.900 align:middle line:90%
You already have the voice.

00:44:34.900 --> 00:44:37.990 align:middle line:84%
Somehow that voice has
been silenced because

00:44:37.990 --> 00:44:40.000 align:middle line:90%
of these generational patterns.

00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:41.560 align:middle line:90%
They silence our voice.

00:44:41.560 --> 00:44:44.140 align:middle line:84%
You need to reach a point
where you are conscious

00:44:44.140 --> 00:44:47.440 align:middle line:90%
and you reclaim that voice.

00:44:47.440 --> 00:44:51.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The experiences that you
were talking about in Africa,

00:44:51.220 --> 00:44:56.200 align:middle line:84%
have those voices being
sequestered and suppressed

00:44:56.200 --> 00:44:58.880 align:middle line:90%
carry through the world.

00:44:58.880 --> 00:44:59.680 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Oh yeah.

00:44:59.680 --> 00:45:02.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To America, which is a
young country, comparatively.

00:45:02.750 --> 00:45:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:45:03.550 --> 00:45:06.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That
imprint with women--

00:45:06.070 --> 00:45:07.510 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: Yeah,
it's still there.

00:45:07.510 --> 00:45:08.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:08.170 --> 00:45:09.670 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: But you
know, when I talk

00:45:09.670 --> 00:45:13.960 align:middle line:84%
about the generational
curses or the wounds

00:45:13.960 --> 00:45:17.950 align:middle line:84%
that we carry and I talk about
the baton that has been passed

00:45:17.950 --> 00:45:21.520 align:middle line:84%
on from my great grandmother,
from her own people

00:45:21.520 --> 00:45:26.890 align:middle line:84%
to my mother and to me, but in
the passing of that ugly baton,

00:45:26.890 --> 00:45:29.140 align:middle line:84%
there's also the
passing of wisdom.

00:45:29.140 --> 00:45:30.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mmm.

00:45:30.110 --> 00:45:30.910 align:middle line:90%
Interesting, yeah.

00:45:30.910 --> 00:45:32.380 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: It's not
only the ugliness.

00:45:32.380 --> 00:45:33.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:45:33.180 --> 00:45:37.060 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: And we have a choice,
as women or as individuals,

00:45:37.060 --> 00:45:39.655 align:middle line:90%
to say of this ugliness--

00:45:39.655 --> 00:45:40.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where's the wisdom.

00:45:40.780 --> 00:45:41.530 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Where's the wisdom.

00:45:41.530 --> 00:45:42.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:42.330 --> 00:45:43.750 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: And carry the wisdom.

00:45:43.750 --> 00:45:44.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:45:44.770 --> 00:45:47.580 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: To dig
into that trauma

00:45:47.580 --> 00:45:50.570 align:middle line:90%
and to find your healing.

00:45:50.570 --> 00:45:53.620 align:middle line:90%
We are healers, as women.

00:45:53.620 --> 00:45:54.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Men too.

00:45:54.590 --> 00:45:55.780 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:45:55.780 --> 00:45:58.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Men too.

00:45:58.300 --> 00:46:01.900 align:middle line:84%
In addition to that, this
idea of bringing your dreams

00:46:01.900 --> 00:46:05.410 align:middle line:84%
to the forefront when
there doesn't appear

00:46:05.410 --> 00:46:10.090 align:middle line:84%
to be the even permission
to have a dream.

00:46:10.090 --> 00:46:12.490 align:middle line:84%
And in many
situations, for those

00:46:12.490 --> 00:46:16.240 align:middle line:84%
that don't have Oprah to
exalt our dreams, what could

00:46:16.240 --> 00:46:19.750 align:middle line:84%
you tell people whose
circumstances don't allow

00:46:19.750 --> 00:46:22.160 align:middle line:84%
for the dream, or they
wouldn't speak it,

00:46:22.160 --> 00:46:24.190 align:middle line:90%
what could you tell them to do?

00:46:24.190 --> 00:46:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: You know,
for me, even when

00:46:27.220 --> 00:46:32.440 align:middle line:84%
Oprah came into my
life, I was already

00:46:32.440 --> 00:46:37.090 align:middle line:84%
on a journey for my own
redemption and my own healing,

00:46:37.090 --> 00:46:39.640 align:middle line:84%
because my grandmother
and my mother

00:46:39.640 --> 00:46:44.680 align:middle line:84%
were telling me about the
importance of owning my voice.

00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:47.380 align:middle line:84%
And my grandmother
would always say

00:46:47.380 --> 00:46:53.170 align:middle line:84%
does your voice match this
dream that you are chasing?

00:46:53.170 --> 00:46:54.880 align:middle line:90%
Does it?

00:46:54.880 --> 00:46:59.800 align:middle line:84%
So I tell women, if
you have a dream,

00:46:59.800 --> 00:47:04.690 align:middle line:84%
do you have the voice
that matches that dream?

00:47:04.690 --> 00:47:06.940 align:middle line:90%
Ask yourself.

00:47:06.940 --> 00:47:13.630 align:middle line:84%
And also, to ask yourself
what soul wounds do I carry?

00:47:13.630 --> 00:47:17.080 align:middle line:84%
Can you confront
those soul wounds?

00:47:17.080 --> 00:47:20.980 align:middle line:84%
How do they manifest
in your current life?

00:47:20.980 --> 00:47:22.700 align:middle line:90%
Are you a victim?

00:47:22.700 --> 00:47:23.500 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:47:23.500 --> 00:47:25.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that
story, it connects

00:47:25.330 --> 00:47:27.280 align:middle line:84%
right to what you're
saying about the voice.

00:47:27.280 --> 00:47:28.360 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:47:28.360 --> 00:47:30.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Are your actions--

00:47:30.580 --> 00:47:31.960 align:middle line:90%
do they match the dream?

00:47:31.960 --> 00:47:33.610 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Exactly.

00:47:33.610 --> 00:47:34.420 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:47:34.420 --> 00:47:36.107 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Huge piece.

00:47:36.107 --> 00:47:36.940 align:middle line:90%
That's a huge piece.

00:47:36.940 --> 00:47:41.950 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: You have to keep
on asking yourself every day.

00:47:41.950 --> 00:47:45.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or are you stuck in
the story of the wounds, which

00:47:45.010 --> 00:47:46.230 align:middle line:90%
is, yes, understandable.

00:47:46.230 --> 00:47:47.030 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:47:47.030 --> 00:47:48.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But are you
repeating that story

00:47:48.790 --> 00:47:50.460 align:middle line:84%
so that it will never
allow you to match

00:47:50.460 --> 00:47:51.460 align:middle line:90%
the energy of the dream?

00:47:51.460 --> 00:47:54.510 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: Because it is a story
that is more comfortable to us.

00:47:54.510 --> 00:47:58.030 align:middle line:84%
It is a story that makes
us a victim, sometimes.

00:47:58.030 --> 00:48:01.540 align:middle line:84%
But we need to say
I am not a victim.

00:48:01.540 --> 00:48:03.750 align:middle line:84%
I am part of the
solution, and here

00:48:03.750 --> 00:48:09.340 align:middle line:84%
is how I want to reshape the
narrative moving forward.

00:48:09.340 --> 00:48:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And the way to
reshape that narrative

00:48:12.130 --> 00:48:15.220 align:middle line:84%
so that I define
who I am, I have

00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:18.820 align:middle line:84%
to confront the
ugliness in my own life

00:48:18.820 --> 00:48:23.860 align:middle line:84%
and be truthful about it and
start sharing these stories

00:48:23.860 --> 00:48:25.690 align:middle line:90%
to this generation.

00:48:25.690 --> 00:48:29.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That helps you match
the voice to the dream.

00:48:29.030 --> 00:48:29.830 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:48:29.830 --> 00:48:33.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is a
huge teaching moment.

00:48:33.210 --> 00:48:36.012 align:middle line:84%
You cannot create the dream
if the voice is down here.

00:48:36.012 --> 00:48:37.095 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: No, you cannot.

00:48:37.095 --> 00:48:41.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have to rise through
the journey and the stories

00:48:41.080 --> 00:48:43.060 align:middle line:90%
and the narrative to match.

00:48:43.060 --> 00:48:43.990 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Exactly.

00:48:43.990 --> 00:48:45.845 align:middle line:90%
And be authentic to it.

00:48:45.845 --> 00:48:46.645 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:48:46.645 --> 00:48:48.650 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Be vulnerable to it.

00:48:48.650 --> 00:48:50.440 align:middle line:90%
Be open to it.

00:48:50.440 --> 00:48:54.460 align:middle line:84%
There's beauty in our
own vulnerability,

00:48:54.460 --> 00:48:57.700 align:middle line:84%
when we can face it and
say this is who I am.

00:48:57.700 --> 00:49:02.080 align:middle line:84%
You know, in my culture
when we greet one another,

00:49:02.080 --> 00:49:08.350 align:middle line:84%
we say [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH],,
I see you.

00:49:08.350 --> 00:49:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And your response is,
I am here to be seen.

00:49:13.960 --> 00:49:18.970 align:middle line:84%
With all my ugliness, with all
my wounds and with all my joy,

00:49:18.970 --> 00:49:21.670 align:middle line:90%
I am here to be seen.

00:49:21.670 --> 00:49:23.127 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what
do you say again?

00:49:23.127 --> 00:49:24.460 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:24.460 --> 00:49:27.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And what would
I say in your language?

00:49:27.570 --> 00:49:28.930 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:28.930 --> 00:49:30.138 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:30.138 --> 00:49:31.600 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:31.600 --> 00:49:35.020 align:middle line:90%
I am here to be seen.

00:49:35.020 --> 00:49:40.730 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to hide from
the ugliness that we carry.

00:49:40.730 --> 00:49:43.150 align:middle line:90%
From our vulnerabilities.

00:49:43.150 --> 00:49:45.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And humbleness,
it carries a humbleness.

00:49:45.550 --> 00:49:45.910 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Exactly.

00:49:45.910 --> 00:49:47.118 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:47.118 --> 00:49:48.850 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:49:48.850 --> 00:49:49.930 align:middle line:90%
I am here to be seen.

00:49:49.930 --> 00:49:51.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I am here to be seen.

00:49:51.260 --> 00:49:52.060 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:49:52.060 --> 00:49:54.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And I appreciate you.

00:49:54.280 --> 00:49:57.762 align:middle line:84%
I have to ask, for
you going forward,

00:49:57.762 --> 00:49:59.470 align:middle line:84%
and I know that it's
not an easy journey,

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:03.130 align:middle line:84%
to carry on a foundation and
to carry through this schools.

00:50:03.130 --> 00:50:03.930 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:50:03.930 --> 00:50:05.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And to carry
on the funding.

00:50:05.520 --> 00:50:07.660 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Yeah.

00:50:07.660 --> 00:50:12.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Your biggest
why, in present time.

00:50:12.620 --> 00:50:15.465 align:middle line:84%
If you could share that with
me, what is the biggest why?

00:50:15.465 --> 00:50:17.530 align:middle line:90%
What moves you every day?

00:50:17.530 --> 00:50:19.270 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Why?

00:50:19.270 --> 00:50:21.610 align:middle line:90%
The ugly baton.

00:50:21.610 --> 00:50:23.770 align:middle line:90%
That's my why.

00:50:23.770 --> 00:50:28.070 align:middle line:84%
We find redemption in
what breaks our heart.

00:50:28.070 --> 00:50:29.290 align:middle line:90%
I've been there.

00:50:29.290 --> 00:50:31.300 align:middle line:90%
I was married young.

00:50:31.300 --> 00:50:35.910 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to see anyone to
go through what I went through.

00:50:35.910 --> 00:50:38.440 align:middle line:90%
And that addresses my why.

00:50:38.440 --> 00:50:42.250 align:middle line:10%
I wake up every
day knowing I have

00:50:42.250 --> 00:50:45.790 align:middle line:10%
a moral and a sacred
responsibility.

00:50:45.790 --> 00:50:49.720 align:middle line:84%
Because my mother
said here on Earth,

00:50:49.720 --> 00:50:54.940 align:middle line:84%
we are climbing an
invisible ladder.

00:50:54.940 --> 00:50:58.660 align:middle line:84%
This ladder is so tall
but it's invisible.

00:50:58.660 --> 00:51:00.550 align:middle line:90%
It is rungs.

00:51:00.550 --> 00:51:03.560 align:middle line:84%
There are others who are
at the bottom of the rung

00:51:03.560 --> 00:51:07.600 align:middle line:84%
and there are others who
are at the top of the rung.

00:51:07.600 --> 00:51:10.360 align:middle line:90%
I am at the top of that rung.

00:51:10.360 --> 00:51:13.510 align:middle line:84%
And my mother would always
say, the invisible ladder,

00:51:13.510 --> 00:51:17.260 align:middle line:90%
it has its own invisible laws.

00:51:17.260 --> 00:51:20.740 align:middle line:10%
You have the moral obligation,
because you are there

00:51:20.740 --> 00:51:25.510 align:middle line:10%
at the top, to pull up
those who are at the bottom.

00:51:25.510 --> 00:51:31.780 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes
living beautiful for me.

00:51:31.780 --> 00:51:34.060 align:middle line:90%
That's what addresses my why.

00:51:34.060 --> 00:51:35.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every day.

00:51:35.050 --> 00:51:35.925 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Every day.

00:51:35.925 --> 00:51:36.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every day.

00:51:36.930 --> 00:51:37.930 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Every day.

00:51:37.930 --> 00:51:44.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I want to thank
you for being the example

00:51:44.770 --> 00:51:46.720 align:middle line:90%
of an awakened woman.

00:51:46.720 --> 00:51:48.730 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: Thank
you, but I stand

00:51:48.730 --> 00:51:50.805 align:middle line:90%
on the shoulders of other women.

00:51:50.805 --> 00:51:52.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And I
honor them as well.

00:51:52.180 --> 00:51:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>>TERERAI: And
other men as well.

00:51:52.750 --> 00:51:53.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:53.070 --> 00:51:53.900 align:middle line:90%
>>TERERAI: Thank you.

00:51:53.900 --> 00:51:54.580 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:51:54.580 --> 00:51:56.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Thank you
so much, and thank

00:51:56.110 --> 00:52:00.370 align:middle line:84%
you so much for sharing this
incredible moment with me

00:52:00.370 --> 00:52:02.830 align:middle line:84%
and for really
learning about what it

00:52:02.830 --> 00:52:05.560 align:middle line:90%
means to achieve your dreams.

